					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">On the NES, DPCM encoded samples <em>intrinsically always</em> encode an audible error signal.<br /><br />For a naÃ¯ve encoder that doesn't try to do any noise shaping (which is to say almost all of them), this error signal is a whine at half the sampling rate.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

